        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[At least 10 Champions Are Getting Buffed in LoL Patch 26.13 Before MSI]]></title>
            <link>https://insider-gaming.com/10-champions-buffed-lol-patch-26-13-before-msi/</link>
            <guid>1552735</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div>
        
<p>Riot Games has released a preview of what <a href="https://insider-gaming.com/category/esports/games/league-of-legends/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">League of Legends</a> players can expect from LoL Patch 26.13.</p>



<p>This update is especially important as it is the update that MSI 2026, one of the biggest esports tournaments of the year, will be played on.</p>



<p>Because of that, underplayed champions like Kindred and Vex are receiving buffs to try and shake up the meta.</p>







<p>It is also the patch that <a href="https://insider-gaming.com/everything-you-need-to-know-about-new-lol-champion-locke/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">new LoL champion Locke</a> will release, the only new character coming to the game this year.</p>



<p>However, while the AP assassin will be terrorising solo queue, he won’t be enabled for the esports event.</p>



<p>If you haven’t already, download the free Insider Gaming App for the cleanest way to read your gaming news on iOS and Android:</p>



<ul>
<li><strong>Android Link:</strong>&nbsp;<a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.insidergaming.app" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.insidergaming.app</a></li>



<li><strong>iOS Link:</strong>&nbsp;<a href="https://apps.apple.com/us/app/insider-gaming/id6753984648" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">https://apps.apple.com/us/app/insider-gaming/id6753984648</a></li>
</ul>



<h2 id="h-phroxzon-explains-upcoming-changes">Phroxzon Explains Upcoming Changes</h2>



<figure><div><blockquote data-width="500" data-dnt="true"><div lang="en" dir="ltr"><p>Patch 26.13 Preview! </p><p>Mostly champion changes today for our final MSI Patch, so going to go a bit lighter on context to chat more about them tomorrow. </p><p>Locke<br>– Locke will also hit the Rift some time during Patch 26.13<br>– We're super excited for his release (I know I will be… <a href="https://t.co/o52eZ6xbzp">pic.twitter.com/o52eZ6xbzp</a></p></div>— Matt Leung-Harrison (@RiotPhroxzon) <a href="https://x.com/RiotPhroxzon/status/2066778743046369780?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">June 16, 2026</a></blockquote></div></figure>



<p>As usual, lead gameplay designer Matt ‘Phroxzon’ Leung-Harrison has previewed the upcoming patch and added some extra context.</p>



<p>As expected, he confirmed Riot is trying to add variety to the pro meta for MSI:</p>



<p>“At a high level, changes this patch are mostly aimed at making some of the fringe picks a little more viable and tailored towards the situations teams might want to pick them, especially in later series of the MSI tournament.”</p>



<ul>
<li><strong>Related News</strong>: <a href="https://insider-gaming.com/riot-games-gifts-newlywed-couple-custom-league-of-legends-plaque/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"><strong>Riot gifted a newly married couple a custom LoL plaque</strong></a></li>
</ul>



<p>Phroxzon added that Imperial Mandate has been picked up by some midlaners like Galio, but wants it to be a more appealing item for supports:</p>



<p>“This set of changes is meant to position it to be more fantasy forward for Support champions while also giving it a bit of a power up.</p>



<p>“It’s not really the ‘best item’ on any support at current tuning and for an item with as strong kit synergies as this, it probably should be if it’s appropriately powerful.”</p>



<h2 id="h-expected-changes-for-lol-patch-26-13">Expected Changes for LoL Patch 26.13</h2>



<ul>
<li><strong>Champion Buffs</strong>
<ul>
<li>Aphelios</li>



<li>Draven</li>



<li>Kai’Sa</li>



<li>Kindred</li>



<li>Le Blanc</li>



<li>Olaf</li>



<li>Poppy</li>



<li>Qiyana</li>



<li>Vex</li>



<li>Zaahen</li>
</ul>
</li>



<li><strong>Champion Nerfs</strong>
<ul>
<li>Bard</li>



<li>Brand</li>



<li>Cassiopeia</li>



<li>K’Sante</li>



<li>Rek’Sai</li>



<li>Rumble</li>



<li>Senna</li>



<li>Sion</li>
</ul>
</li>



<li><strong>System Buffs</strong>
<ul>
<li>Imperial Mandate</li>
</ul>
</li>



<li><strong>System Nerfs</strong>
<ul>
<li>Doran’s Helm</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>







<p>Which champion would you like to see become meta in pro play? Share your thoughts on the&nbsp;<a href="https://discord.com/invite/vwj7zdWxaW)" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Insider Gaming Discord</a>.</p>



<hr>



<p>Meanwhile, the most recent&nbsp;<a href="https://insider-gaming.com/lol-dev-update-locke-ranked-5s-and-mayhem-traits-removed/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">LoL dev update revealed traits are gone from ARAM Mayhem and Ranked 5s are returning</a>.</p>


        
            

